text:
Second Avenue, east side, north from 108th Street. October 17, 1934.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

(1)
Feast of Our Lady of Mt. Carmel: The band leading the paraders in their march to the shrine of Our Lady of Mt. Carmel. This view was taken in a westward direction on East 108th Street.

July 16, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The line of march crossing Second Ave. and proceeding eastward on East 110th Street.

July 16, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same as No. 2.

July 16, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Feast of Our Lady of Mount Carmel.
